This paper is about designing a lightweight semantic segmentation network using a novel search mechanism with a new search space. The paper focuses on computer vision (CV) tasks, specifically semantic segmentation, which suggests that cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a graph convolution network (GCN) as a communication mechanism between cells, which is a popular topic in machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL) research, indicating that cs.LG and cs.AI are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves optimizing the network for speed and performance, which is a common theme in robotics (RO) and neural networks (NE) research, making these sub-categories also likely.
